<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910927-0071</DOCNO><DOCID>910927-0071.</DOCID><HL>   Sansui Electric Posts   1st-Half Pretax Loss   Totaling $25.5 Million</HL><DATE>09/27/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   J.SNE U.POL</CO><MS>CONGLOMERATES (CGL)INDUSTRIAL (IDU)CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)CONGLOMERATES (CGL)ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)EARNINGS (ERN)FOOD PRODUCTS (FOD)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>BANKRUPTCY DECLARATIONS AND PROCEEDINGS (BCY)EARNINGS (ERN)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)FAR EAST (FE)HONG KONG (HK)JAPAN (JA)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Sansui Electric Co., the struggling Japaneseaudio-products maker, reported an unconsolidated pretax lossof 3.40 billion yen ($25.5 million) for the first half endedJune 30, widening from a 2.94-billion-yen loss during theyear-earlier fiscal first half, which ended Sept. 30, 1990.   Sansui, majority owned by Polly Peck International PLC ofthe U.K., blamed fierce competition, high costs andstagnating sales for its continued losses.</LP><TEXT>   The Japanese company attributed the worsening of its netloss during the half to a 20.1 billion yen extraordinary lossfor funds set aside for investment losses by subsidiaries.   Sansui, noting that Polly Peck is itself in receivership,said it will strive to boost its results and improve theBritish parent's return on its investment.   Separately, Sansui's president, Tatsuya Inamiya, saidPolly Peck receivers have agreed to sell part of the Sansuiholding to a Hong Kong conglomerate named Grande Group. Theamount of shares to be sold wasn't disclosed, but it willaffect no more than one-third of all the Sansui shares,meaning Polly Peck will retain its status as majority owner,he said.   The company said unconsolidated sales of audio equipmentrose 3.8% to 8.007 billion yen, or 90% of its total sales forthe half. Video equipment sales rose 34% to 609 million yen,or 6.9% of the total.   For the full year ending Dec. 31, Sansui predicts it willpost a 6 billion yen pretax loss and a 19 billion yen netloss. Due to the change in the company's fiscal period,year-on-year comparisons aren't available. Sales of 26.0billion yen are expected.   On a consolidated basis, Sansui said it posted afirst-half pretax loss of 7.19 billion yen, worse than a9.21-billion-yen loss the year before. The company posted anet loss of 23.20 billion yen, or 143.47 yen per share, worsethan the 8.99 billion yen loss, or 67.41 yen a share, theyear before. Sales fell to 42.939 billion yen from 62.457billion yen.   For the full year through December 31, Sansui expects an 8billion yen pretax loss, a 22 billion yen net loss and salesof 110.00 billion yen.</TEXT></DOC>